# File and Folder Structure Naming Convention

## Naming

- Use `kebab-case` for all file names and folder names.
- Avoid spaces, underscores, and camelCase/PascalCase in folder and file paths.

## Page Location

- Store all pages in `src/pages`.
- Each page should live in its own folder under `src/pages`.

## Subpages

- If a page has subpages, place them under `src/pages/{page-name}/(sub-pages)/{sub-page-name}`.
- Keep subpage file/folder names in `kebab-case`.
- Do not create a `parts` folder inside subpages.

## Component Placement

- Put shared components used across multiple pages in `src/components`.
- Put page-scoped components (used by one page and/or its subpages) only in `src/pages/{page-name}/parts`.
- The `parts` folder is allowed only at the main page folder level.

## Parts File Naming

- Files inside `src/pages/{page-name}/parts` must follow `{page-name}-{description}.tsx`.
- Keep `{description}` in `kebab-case`.
- Examples:
  - `dashboard-widgets.tsx`
  - `analytics-chard-cards.tsx`

## Example Structure

```text
src/
  components/
    app-header/
      app-header.tsx
    empty-state/
      empty-state.tsx
  pages/
    dashboard/
      page.tsx
      parts/
        dashboard-summary-card.tsx
        dashboard-widgets.tsx
        analytics-chard-cards.tsx
      (sub-pages)/
        analytics/
          page.tsx
    account-settings/
      page.tsx
      parts/
        profile-form.tsx
```

## Quick Checks

- New path uses `kebab-case`.
- New page is under `src/pages/{page-name}`.
- Shared UI goes to `src/components`.
- Page-only UI goes to `src/pages/{page-name}/parts` (main page folder only).
- Subpages follow `src/pages/{page-name}/(sub-pages)/{sub-page-name}`.
- Subpages do not have their own `parts` folder.
- Parts files follow `{page-name}-{description}.tsx`.
